ipspEspTranReplayWindowSize.description: ipspEspTranReplayWindowSize indicates the size, in bits, of the replay window to use if replay protection is true for this transform. The window size is assumed to be a power of two. If Replay Protection is false, this value can be ignored.

ipspEspTranLastChanged.name: ipspEspTranLastChanged
ipspEspTranLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when this row was last modified or created either through SNMP SETs or by some other external means.

ipspEspTranStorageType.name: ipspEspTranStorageType
ipspEspTranStorageType.description: The storage type for this row. Rows in this table which were created through an external process may have a storage type of readOnly or permanent.

ipspEspTranRowStatus.name: ipspEspTranRowStatus
ipspEspTranRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified. If active, this object must remain active if it is referenced by a row in another table.

ipspIpcompTransformTable.name: ipspIpcompTransformTable
ipspIpcompTransformTable.description: This table lists all the IP compression transforms which can be used to build IPsec proposals during negotiation of a phase 2 SA.

ipspIpcompTransformEntry.name: ipspIpcompTransformEntry
ipspIpcompTransformEntry.description: This entry contains the attributes of one IP compression transform.

ipspIpcompTranMaxLifetimeSec.name: ipspIpcompTranMaxLifetimeSec
ipspIpcompTranMaxLifetimeSec.description: ipspIpcompTranMaxLifetimeSec specifies how long in seconds the security association derived from this transform should be used. A value of 0 indicates that the default lifetime of 8 hours should be used.

ipspIpcompTranMaxLifetimeKB.name: ipspIpcompTranMaxLifetimeKB
ipspIpcompTranMaxLifetimeKB.description: ipspIpcompTranMaxLifetimeKB specifies how long in kilobytes the security association derived from this transform should be used.

ipspIpcompTranAlgorithm.name: ipspIpcompTranAlgorithm
ipspIpcompTranAlgorithm.description: ipspIpcompTranAlgorithm specifies the transform ID of the IP compression algorithm.

ipspIpcompTranDictionarySize.name: ipspIpcompTranDictionarySize
ipspIpcompTranDictionarySize.description: If the algorithm in ipspIpcompTranAlgorithm requires a dictionary size configuration parameter, then this is the place to put it. This object specifies the log2 maximum size of the dictionary for the compression algorithm.

ipspIpcompTranPrivateAlgorithm.name: ipspIpcompTranPrivateAlgorithm
ipspIpcompTranPrivateAlgorithm.description: If ipspIpcompTranPrivateAlgorithm has a value other zero, then it is up to the vendors implementation to determine the meaning of this field and substitute a data compression algorithm in place of ipspIpcompTranAlgorithm.

ipspIpcompTranLastChanged.name: ipspIpcompTranLastChanged
ipspIpcompTranLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when this row was last modified or created either through SNMP SETs or by some other external means.

ipspIpcompTranStorageType.name: ipspIpcompTranStorageType
ipspIpcompTranStorageType.description: The storage type for this row. Rows in this table which were created through an external process may have a storage type of readOnly or permanent.

ipspIpcompTranRowStatus.name: ipspIpcompTranRowStatus
ipspIpcompTranRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified. If active, this object must remain active if it is referenced by a row in another table.

ipspIkeIdentityTable.name: ipspIkeIdentityTable
ipspIkeIdentityTable.description: IKEIdentity is used to represent the identities that may be used for an IPProtocolEndpoint (or collection of IPProtocolEndpoints) to identify itself in IKE phase 1 negotiations. The column ikeIdentityName in an ipspIkeActionEntry together with the ipspEndGroupIdentType and the ipspEndGroupAddress in the PolicyEndpointToGroupTable specifies the unique identity to use in a negotiation exchange.

ipspIkeIdentityEntry.name: ipspIkeIdentityEntry
ipspIkeIdentityEntry.description: ikeIdentity lists the attributes of an IKE identity.

ipspIkeIdCredentialName.name: ipspIkeIdCredentialName
ipspIkeIdCredentialName.description: This value is used as an index into the ipspCredentialTable to look up the actual credential value and other credential information. For ID's without associated credential information, this value is left blank. For ID's that are address types, this value may be left blank and the associated IPProtocolEndpoint or appropriate member of the Collection of endpoints is used.

ipspIkeIdLastChanged.name: ipspIkeIdLastChanged
ipspIkeIdLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when this row was last modified or created either through SNMP SETs or by some other external means.

ipspIkeIdStorageType.name: ipspIkeIdStorageType
ipspIkeIdStorageType.description: The storage type for this row. Rows in this table which were created through an external process may have a storage type of readOnly or permanent.

ipspIkeIdRowStatus.name: ipspIkeIdRowStatus
ipspIkeIdRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified. If active, this object must remain active if it is referenced by a row in another table.

ipspPeerIdentityTable.name: ipspPeerIdentityTable
ipspPeerIdentityTable.description: PeerIdentity is used to represent the identities that may be used for peers to identify themselves in IKE phase I/II negotiations. PeerIdentityTable aggregates the table entries that provide mappings between identities and their addresses.

ipspPeerIdentityEntry.name: ipspPeerIdentityEntry
ipspPeerIdentityEntry.description: peerIdentity matches a peer's identity to its address.

ipspPeerIdName.name: ipspPeerIdName
ipspPeerIdName.description: This is an administratively assigned value that, together with ipspPeerIdPriority, uniquely identifies an entry in this table.

ipspPeerIdPriority.name: ipspPeerIdPriority
ipspPeerIdPriority.description: This object, along with ipspPeerIdName, uniquely identifies an entry in this table. The priority also indicates the order of peer gateways to initiate or accept SAs from (i.e. try until success).

ipspPeerIdType.name: ipspPeerIdType
ipspPeerIdType.description: ipspPeerIdType is an enumeration identifying the type of the Identity value.

ipspPeerIdValue.name: ipspPeerIdValue
ipspPeerIdValue.description: ipspPeerIdValue contains an Identity filter to be used to match against the identity payload in an IKE request. If this value matches the value in the identity payload, the credential for the peer can be found using the ipspPeerIdCredentialName as an index into the credential table.

ipspPeerIdAddressType.name: ipspPeerIdAddressType
ipspPeerIdAddressType.description: The property ipspPeerIdAddressType specifies the format of the ipspPeerIdAddress property value.

ipspPeerIdAddress.name: ipspPeerIdAddress
ipspPeerIdAddress.description: The property PeerAddress specifies the IP address of the peer. The format is specified by the ipspPeerIdAddressType. Values of unknown, ipv4z, ipv6z and dns are not legal values for this object.

ipspPeerIdCredentialName.name: ipspPeerIdCredentialName
ipspPeerIdCredentialName.description: This value is used as an index into the ipspCredentialTable to look up the actual credential value and other credential information. For peer IDs that have no associated credential information, this value is left blank.

ipspPeerIdLastChanged.name: ipspPeerIdLastChanged
ipspPeerIdLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when this row was last modified or created either through SNMP SETs or by some other external means.

ipspPeerIdStorageType.name: ipspPeerIdStorageType
ipspPeerIdStorageType.description: The storage type for this row. Rows in this table which were created through an external process may have a storage type of readOnly or permanent.

ipspPeerIdRowStatus.name: ipspPeerIdRowStatus
ipspPeerIdRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified. If active, this object must remain active if it is referenced by a row in another table.

ipspAutostartIkeTable.name: ipspAutostartIkeTable
ipspAutostartIkeTable.description: The parameters in the autostart IKE Table are used to automatically initiate IKE phaes I and II (i.e. IPsec) negotiations on startup. It also will initiate IKE phase I and II negotiations for a row at the time of that row's creation

ipspAutostartIkeEntry.name: ipspAutostartIkeEntry
ipspAutostartIkeEntry.description: autostart ike provides the set of parameters to automatically start IKE and IPsec SA's.

ipspAutoIkePriority.name: ipspAutoIkePriority
ipspAutoIkePriority.description: ipspAutoIkePriority is an index into the autostartIkeAction table and can be used to order the autostart IKE actions.

ipspAutoIkeAction.name: ipspAutoIkeAction
ipspAutoIkeAction.description: This pointer is used to point to the action or compound action that should be initiated by this row.

ipspAutoIkeAddressType.name: ipspAutoIkeAddressType
ipspAutoIkeAddressType.description: The property ipspAutoIkeAddressType specifies the format of the autoIke source and destination Address values. Values of unknown, ipv4z, ipv6z and dns are not legal values for this object.

ipspAutoIkeSourceAddress.name: ipspAutoIkeSourceAddress
ipspAutoIkeSourceAddress.description: The property autoIkeSourecAddress specifies Source IP address for autostarting IKE SA's, formatted according to the appropriate convention as defined in the ipspAutoIkeAddressType property.

ipspAutoIkeSourcePort.name: ipspAutoIkeSourcePort
ipspAutoIkeSourcePort.description: The property ipspAutoIkeSourcePort specifies the port number for the source port for auotstarting IKE SA's. The value of 0 for this object is illegal.

ipspAutoIkeDestAddress.name: ipspAutoIkeDestAddress
ipspAutoIkeDestAddress.description: The property ipspAutoIkeDestAddress specifies the Destination IP address for autostarting IKE SA's, formatted according to the appropriate convention as defined in the ipspAutoIkeAddressType property.

ipspAutoIkeDestPort.name: ipspAutoIkeDestPort
ipspAutoIkeDestPort.description: The property ipspAutoIkeDestPort specifies the port number for the destination port for auotstarting IKE SA's. The value of 0 for this object is illegal.

ipspAutoIkeProtocol.name: ipspAutoIkeProtocol
ipspAutoIkeProtocol.description: The property Protocol specifies the protocol number used in comparing with policy filter entries and used in any phase 2 negotiations.

ipspAutoIkeLastChanged.name: ipspAutoIkeLastChanged
ipspAutoIkeLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when this row was last modified or created either through SNMP SETs or by some other external means.

ipspAutoIkeStorageType.name: ipspAutoIkeStorageType
ipspAutoIkeStorageType.description: The storage type for this row. Rows in this table which were created through an external process may have a storage type of readOnly or permanent.

ipspAutoIkeRowStatus.name: ipspAutoIkeRowStatus
ipspAutoIkeRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

ipspIpsecCredMngServiceTable.name: ipspIpsecCredMngServiceTable
ipspIpsecCredMngServiceTable.description: A table of Credential Management Service values. This table is usually used for credential/certificate values that are used with a management service (e.g. Certificate Authorities).

ipspIcmsName.name: ipspIcmsName
ipspIcmsName.description: This is an administratively assigned string used to index this table.

ipspIcmsDistinguishedName.name: ipspIcmsDistinguishedName
ipspIcmsDistinguishedName.description: This value represents the Distinguished Name of the Credential Management Service.

ipspIcmsPolicyStatement.name: ipspIcmsPolicyStatement
ipspIcmsPolicyStatement.description: This Value represents the Credential Management Service Policy Statement, or a reference describing how to obtain it (e.g., a URL). If one doesn't exist, this value can be left blank

ipspIcmsMaxChainLength.name: ipspIcmsMaxChainLength
ipspIcmsMaxChainLength.description: This value is the maximum length of the chain allowble from the Credential Management Service to the credential in question.

ipspIcmsCredentialName.name: ipspIcmsCredentialName
ipspIcmsCredentialName.description: This value is used as an index into the ipspCredentialTable to look up the actual credential value.

ipspIcmsLastChanged.name: ipspIcmsLastChanged
ipspIcmsLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when this row was last modified or created either through SNMP SETs or by some other external means.

ipspIcmsStorageType.name: ipspIcmsStorageType

ipspActionNotification.name: ipspActionNotification
ipspActionNotification.description: Notification that an action was executed by a rule. Only actions with logging enabled will result in this notification getting sent. The objects sent must include the ipspActionExecuted object which will indicate which action was executed within the scope of the rule. Additionally the ipspIPSourceType, ipspIPSourceAddress, ipspIPDestinationType, and ipspIPDestinationAddress objects must be included to indicate the packet source and destination of the packet that triggered the action. Finally the ipspIPInterfaceType, ipspIPInterfaceAddress, and ipspPacketDirection objects are included to indicate which interface the action was executed in association with and if the packet was inbound or outbond through the endpoint. Note that compound actions with multiple executed subactions may result in multiple notifications being sent from a single rule execution.

ipspPacketNotification.name: ipspPacketNotification
ipspPacketNotification.description: Notification that a packet passed through an SA. Only SA's created by actions with packet logging enabled will result in this notification getting sent. The objects sent must include the ipspActionExecuted which will indicate which action was executed within the scope of the rule. Additionally, the ipspIPSourceType, ipspIPSourceAddress, ipspIPDestinationType, and ipspIPDestinationAddress, objects must be included to indicate the packet source and destination of the packet that triggered the action. The ipspIPInterfaceType, ipspIPInterfaceAddress, and ipspPacketDirection objects are included to indicate which endpoint the packet was associated with. Finally, ipspPacketPart is including for sending a variable sized part of the front of the packet depending on the value of IpspIPPacketLogging.
